name: For Those Who Missed Angels
description: This piece is about unrequited love and those who miss out on angels. Animated from two paintings Nicholas Maes’ “An Old Woman Dozing over a Book” and Titian’s “The Wheel Of Time” both images were made public domain by the National Gallery. The sounds in the background are a creaking door and an untuned cello. The poem is “The Angel” by William Blake. All unclaimed editions will be burnt April 26th.
